{{unreferenced|date=October 2013}} {{Infobox sport governing body |name = Macedonian Volleyball Federation |abbrev = |logo = |logosize = 150px |sport = [[File:Volleyball pictogram.svg|20px]] [[Volleyball]] |category = |image = |caption = |jurisdiction = [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]] |founded = {{Start date|1946}} |aff = [[Fédération Internationale de Volleyball|FIVB]] |affdate = {{Start date|1947}} |region = |regionyear = |headquarters = |location = {{flag|Macedonia}} |president = |chairman = |chairperson = |chair = |chiefexec = |secretary = |coach = |womenscoach = |key staff = |operating income = |sponsor = |year closed = |replaced = |prevfounded = |url = http://www.ofm.com.mk |countryflag = Macedonia }}
'''Volleyball Federation''' was established in 1946 in the framework of physical culture Association of Macedonia. It was one of the founding members of the [[World Volleyball Federation]] (FIVB) (with Belgium, Brazil, Egypt, France, the Netherlands, Hungary, Italy, Poland, Portugal, Romania, Uruguay and the US). On 13 February 1949, the Macedonian volleyball federation has become an independent sports organization.
