{{unreferenced|date=May 2017}} {| class="infobox football" style="width: 16em; text-align: center;" |- ! style="font-size: 16px;" | 1st Slovak National Football League |- | style="font-size: 12px; background: #BFD7FF;" | '''Founded''' |- | style="font-size: 12px;" | 1969 |- | style="font-size: 12px; background: #BFD7FF;" | '''Dissolved''' |- | style="font-size: 12px;" | 1993 |- | style="font-size: 12px; background: #BFD7FF;" | '''Nation''' |- | style="font-size: 12px;" | [[Czechoslovakia]] |- | style="font-size: 12px; background: #BFD7FF;" | '''Level on Pyramid''' |- | style="font-size: 12px;" | Level 2 |- | style="font-size: 12px; background: #BFD7FF;" | '''Promotion To''' |- | style="font-size: 12px;" | [[Czechoslovak First League]] |- | style="font-size: 12px; background: #BFD7FF;" | '''Relegation To''' |- | style="font-size: 12px;" | [[2nd Slovak National Football League]] |- | style="font-size: 12px; background: #BFD7FF;" | '''Number of Seasons''' |- | style="font-size: 12px;" | 24 |- | style="font-size: 12px; background: #BFD7FF;" | '''Last Champions 1992-93''' |- | style="font-size: 12px;" | [[1. FC Košice]] |- | style="font-size: 12px; background: #BFD7FF;" | '''Replaced by''' |- | style="font-size: 12px;" | [[2. Liga (Slovakia)]] |- |}
The '''Slovak National Football League''' was the second-tier [[Association football|football]] league of [[Czechoslovakia]] and the top division in [[Slovak Socialist Republic]].
==History== * 1969 – Founded as ''3. liga, skupina "C"'' (Czechoslovak third league, group C) * 1974 – Renamed ''Slovenská národná futbalová liga'' (Slovak national football league) * 1981 – Renamed ''1. slovenská národná futbalová liga'' (Slovak first national football league) * 1993 – Dissolved. Top 6 teams created the new [[Slovak Super Liga]], along with all 6 Slovak teams from [[Czechoslovak First League]].
